Seems like these are for the join column names? As I mentioned earlier, we can use a custom naming strategy without breaking any backward compatibility.
Sorry I didn't catch this part when I looked earlier at this review.
I was planning to push the stuff in PAP, but its taking time to finish off other things before that. So I will put the code here so that you can try.

import org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.Identifier;
import org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.ImplicitJoinColumnNameSource;
import org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.ImplicitNamingStrategyJpaCompliantImpl;

public class CustomImplicitNamingStrategy extends ImplicitNamingStrategyJpaCompliantImpl{
    @Override
    public Identifier determineJoinColumnName(ImplicitJoinColumnNameSource source) {
        String name = source.getReferencedColumnName().getText();
        return toIdentifier( name, source.getBuildingContext() );
    }
}

Use this in your spring boot hibernate code, and see if it is working
Basically the idea is to avoid breaking any backward compatibility (If Possible).
